; S-04 weave_log field projections
;
; Six tiny Forms, one per Entry field that S-04/append projects
; in its body. Each is 5-10 instructions of IL: read the entry,
; project the named field, return.
;
; The encoded primary Form S-04-weave-log.form references each
; of these via READSLOT name + CALL. STUBS.md catalogues each
; one as v0.2.0-helpers work; this is the first batch.
;
; Synthesis chain:
;   provocation:  STUBS.md item "Helpers required by S-04
;                 weave_log" lists six projection helpers as
;                 pending. Each one is small enough that the
;                 design has only one candidate; the breakdown
;                 dependence is "the projection extracts the
;                 named field from the Entry record per the
;                 weave entry layout".
;   grounding:    A1.2 (type is intrinsic — the projection
;                 trusts the type tag), A6.1 (a unit of code is
;                 a substance — these are small Forms like any
;                 other), A0.6 (code is thought, not artifact)
;   composes_with: nothing — these are pure leaves
;
; Each projection has the same shape:
;   :declared-caps (S-03/ROOT_RO)        ; only needs READ
;   :declared-traps (ETYPE)              ; trap if not an Entry
;   :arity 1                             ; (entry_hash) on stack
;   body: READ → project field → RET
;
; The projections are sealed individually so each can be
; verified by S-08 against its declared-caps line in isolation.
; A reviewer of the inspection record can verify all six in
; under a minute by enumerating their bodies.

; ============================================================
; S-04/proj/prev — extract entry.prev
; ============================================================

(form
  :type-tag      "Form/v1"
  :name          "proj_prev"
  :declared-caps (S-03/ROOT_RO)
  :declared-traps (ETYPE)
  :arity         1
  :locals-n      2
  :code (
    STORE   0                   ; entry hash
    LOAD    0
    READ                        ; → entry bytes
    STORE   1
    LOAD    1
    PUSH    "Entry/proj/prev"
    SEAL    Hash
    READSLOT
    CALL    h=$ /n=1            ; → field bytes via the entry-record schema helper
    RET
  )
  :rationale-hash $$BLAKE3$$/s04-projections-rationale
)

